If we go down the road of legalisation and harm reduction, as proposed in this report, then we would see the problem exacerbated a hundredfold across all our cities.
The issue here is not about a mix-and-match of best policies.
The issue is about information to show people the damage and dangers that they face if they get involved in drugs.
The issue is about strong criminal penalties to ensure that those who traffic in drugs are hit where it hurts: in their pockets.
