Â Â  Mr President, it is very late now and very few of us are left but nevertheless we are dealing with a very important issue.
It is a pity that once again in this Parliament legislation is left until the end of the day.
In a recent opinion poll 77Â per cent of British people said that they are concerned about pesticides in food so, as everyone has said, what we are doing here resonates with public opinion.
